#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_managing.xml:978
#, no-c-format
msgid "Migrating &vmguest;s"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:980
#, no-c-format
msgid "One of the major advantages of virtualization is that &vmguest;s are portable. When a &vmhost; needs to go down for maintenance, or when the host gets overloaded, the guests can easily be moved to another &vmhost;. &kvm; and &xen; even support <quote>live</quote> migrations during which the &vmguest; is constantly available."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_managing.xml:989
#, no-c-format
msgid "Migration requirements"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:990
#, no-c-format
msgid "To successfully migrate a &vmguest; to another &vmhost;, the following requirements need to be met:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:995
#, no-c-format
msgid "In order to use the post-copy live migration option, &kvm; hosts with kernel version 5.11 or newer require setting the <varname>unprivileged_userfaultfd</varname> system value to <literal>1</literal> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: libvirt_managing.xml:1001
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;sysctl -w vm.unprivileged_userfaultfd=1"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:1002
#, no-c-format
msgid "Since kernel versions prior to 5.11 did not require setting unprivileged_userfaultfd to use the post-copy option, &libvirt; provides the setting in <filename>/usr/lib/sysctl.d/60-qemu-postcopy-migration.conf</filename> file to preserve the old behavior."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:1011
#, no-c-format
msgid "The source and destination systems must have the same architecture."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:1016
#, no-c-format
msgid "Storage devices must be accessible from both machines (for example, via NFS or iSCSI) and must be configured as a storage pool on both machines. For more information, see <xref linkend=\"cha-libvirt-storage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:1021
#, no-c-format
msgid "This is also true for CD-ROM or floppy images that are connected during the move. However, you can disconnect them prior to the move as described in <xref linkend=\"sec-libvirt-config-cdrom-media-change\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:1028
#, no-c-format
msgid "&libvirtd; needs to run on both &vmhost;s and you must be able to open a remote &libvirt; connection between the target and the source host (or vice versa). Refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-libvirt-connect-remote\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:1036
#, no-c-format
msgid "If a firewall is running on the target host, ports need to be opened to allow the migration. If you do not specify a port during the migration process, &libvirt; chooses one from the range 49152:49215. Make sure that either this range (recommended) or a dedicated port of your choice is opened in the firewall on the <emphasis>target host</emphasis> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:1045
#, no-c-format
msgid "Host and target machine should be in the same subnet on the network, otherwise networking will not work after the migration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:1051
#, no-c-format
msgid "All &vmhost;s participating in migration must have the same UID for the qemu user and the same GIDs for the kvm, qemu, and libvirt groups."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:1057
#, no-c-format
msgid "No running or paused &vmguest; with the same name must exist on the target host. If a shut down machine with the same name exists, its configuration will be overwritten."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:1064
#, no-c-format
msgid "All CPU models except <emphasis>host cpu</emphasis> model are supported when migrating &vmguest;s."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:1070
#, no-c-format
msgid "<xref linkend=\"gloss-vt-acronym-sata\"/> disk device type is not migratable."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:1076
#, no-c-format
msgid "File system pass-through feature is incompatible with migration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:1081
#, no-c-format
msgid "The &vmhost; and &vmguest; need to have proper timekeeping installed. See <xref linkend=\"sec-kvm-managing-clock\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:1087
#, no-c-format
msgid "No physical devices can be passed from host to guest. Live migration is currently not supported when using devices with PCI pass-through or <xref linkend=\"vt-io-sriov\"/> . If live migration needs to be supported, you need to use software virtualization (paravirtualization or full virtualization)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:1096
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cache mode setting is an important setting for migration. See: <xref linkend=\"sec-cache-mode-live-migration\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:1102
#, no-c-format
msgid "Backward migration (for example, from &slsa; 15 SP2 to 15 SP1) is not supported."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:1108
#, no-c-format
msgid "SUSE strives to support live migration of &vmguest;s from a &vmhost; running a service pack under LTSS to a &vmhost; running a newer service pack, within the same &slsa; major version. For example, &vmguest; migration from an &slsa; 12 SP2 host to an &slsa; 12 SP5 host. SUSE only performs minimal testing of LTSS-to-newer migration scenarios and recommends thorough on-site testing before attempting to migrate critical &vmguest;s."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_managing.xml:1119
#, no-c-format
msgid "The image directory should be located in the same path on both hosts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
